isoiec80000:term-t2-10.11-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "power"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t2-10.11-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "root(n)(a)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t2-10.11 a isoiec80000:MathConcept, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "2-10.11" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t2-10.11-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t2-10.11-0 ;
  skos:definition """stem:[n]^th^ root of stem:[a]"""@en ;
  skos:note """If stem:[a >= 0], then stem:[root(n)(a) >= 0].

The symbol without the upper line stem:[root(n)(a)] should be avoided.

If however the symbol stem:[root(n)(\" \")] or stem:[sqrt] is used acting on a composite expression, parentheses shall be used to avoid ambiguity.
"""@en ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-2-10 .